title: Beatles 1967-1970 Blue Album @160
description: Picking up where 1962-1966 left off, the double-album compilation 1967-1970, commonly called the &quot;Blue Album,&quot; covers the Beatles' later records, from Sgt. Pepper through Let It Be. Like the Red Album, the Blue Album contains a mixture of hits, including singles like &quot;Lady Madonna,&quot; &quot;Hey Jude,&quot; and &quot;Revolution&quot; that were never included on an LP, plus important album tracks like &quot;Lucy in the Sky with Diamonds,&quot; &quot;A Day in the Life,&quot; &quot;While My Guitar Gently Weeps,&quot; and &quot;Come Together.&quot; Like its predecessor, 1967-1970 misses several great songs, but the compilation nevertheless does capture the essence of the Beatles' later recordings.
